<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-69-0298 </DOCNO><TEXT>By the end of the century, Community countries will have to reduce thelevel of noxious emissions into the atmosphere from large-scale combustionplant and from motor vehicles with an engine capacity of below 1400 cc.This compromise is the result of the agreement reached in Brussels byenvironment ministers last June and marks an important step in the fightagainst acid rain, which is the main cause of the destruction of a largepart of the forest heritage of Central Europe.</TEXT></DOC>